                        All personal data collected from you may be transferred to and stored outside the European Economic Area (“EEA”). This includes destinations not encompassed by the European Commission regarding an adequate level of protection for processing personal data. It may be disclosed to other products within Randomness LTD, managed by Randomness LTD employees or employees working for suppliers of Randomness LTD outside the EEA. Such staff can be involved in processing your order, payment information and/or performing support services for Randomness LTD, among other services. All reasonable precautions are taken to ensure that your personal data is handled in a safe manner and in accordance with our Privacy Policy, taking appropriate measures to protect all your personal information. For more information about our Privacy Policy or to obtain a copy of these measures, please contact us using the contact information found at the bottom of this Privacy Policy.<br><br>
