                        <b>How can we Secure Your Personal Data?</b><br>
                        Protecting your personal information is vital to us and a primary concern at Randomness LTD. All personal data provided by you is stored on secure servers and we follow strict procedures in order to safeguard all data against abuse, unauthorized access, loss, disclosure or deletion/destruction. All payment transactions are encrypted with the help of industry standard technology and subject to PCI security standards.<br>
                        Although we work hard to safeguard your personal information, we are unable to fully guarantee that our internal security measures will prevent all unauthorized attempts to use, access or disclose your personal information. That said, we have developed specific safety plans, including strategies for managing any breach of data security, that are implemented if and when such a physical or technical incident should occur in order to handle the issue in a timely fashion and restrict any negative effect that said incident might cause.<br><br>
                        <b>How do you Access Your Own Personal Information?</b><br>
                        We understand that there are times when you will need additional information from us regarding your personal data and how it is processed. Other times you may wish to update the personal information you have already provided for us. With respect to the management of personal data, you are entitled to the following:<br>
                        You have the right to access all your personal information. You have the right to be informed by us when and if we process personal data about you and, if so, to access such data.<br>
                        You have the right to have personal information corrected and/or updated: If you should find that the personal information we have stored about you is incorrect, you have the full right to request an update and/or correction of such personal data. <br>
                        You have the right to have your personal information deleted: Under certain circumstances, for instance if your personal data has been acquired or processed in a fraudulent or illegal manner or if you have withdrawn your consent (when the processing of personal data is based on prior customer consent), you have the right to request that we delete your personal information. <br>
                        You have the right to restrict the processing of personal information: under certain circumstances, for instance if you should disagree with the accuracy of your personal information or if you should object to our legitimate purpose for processing your personal data, you have the right to request that we restrict the use and/or processing of your personal data until an appropriate solution has been found.<br>
                        You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data: under certain circumstances, for instance if you should disagree with our legitimate interest in processing your personal data, you have the right to contend such processing.<br>
                        You have the right to data portability: If your personal data is being processed automatically with your consent or on the basis of our contractual relationship, you are entitled to request a copy of your personal data in a machine-readable format for the transmission to an external data controller.<br>
                        You have the right to file a complaint with your supervisory authority: In case you should disagree with the manner in which we process your personal data, you may file a complaint with your supervisory authority.<br>
                        If we should process your personal information on the basis of your prior consent, you are still entitled to withdraw such consent at any time (it will not affect the data that has already been processed prior to your withdrawal) by contacting us or by updating your settings.<br>
                        If you wish to make a request, please contact us by using the contact details at the bottom of this document. We will do our best to respond to your request within 30 days of receiving it. If we are unable to comply with your request within 30 days, we will inform you of the situation, the reason for such a delay and when we expect to be able to fulfil your request.
